title: Textile, 19th century
medium:
Medium: cotton, tin edging
Technique: tied resist patterning in weft (ikat) on plain weave; discontinuous supplementary weft patterning (brocade)
dimensions: Warp x Weft: 167.6 x 36.8 cm (66 x 14 1/2 in.)
description: Narrow textile, probably a breast cloth (kemben), with ikat warp-printed center. In black, red, and white. Ends brocaded and warps gathered in tin edging.
